---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/home.css';

// NOTE: Baseline / starting-template legal text drafted from the app's actual
// stack (Clerk, Stripe, PostHog, DigitalOcean, TMDB/Jikan). Self-hosted so it
// can't lapse like the old iubenda link. Review before relying on it legally;
// replace/refine with Termly- or lawyer-reviewed text when ready. Two spots
// need your input: the governing-law jurisdiction and your refund stance.

const title = 'Terms of Service - ShowShowShow';
const description = 'Terms of Service for ShowShowShow';
const appUrl = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_APP_URL || 'https://app.showshowshow.app';
const effectiveDate = 'June 29, 2026';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="page">
    <header class="nav">
      <div class="nav-container">
        <a class="brand" href="/">ShowShowShow</a>
        <div class="nav-menu">
          <nav class="nav-links">
            <a href="/">Home</a>
            <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
            <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
          </nav>
          <a class="btn primary nav-cta-btn" href="/#waitlist">Join waitlist</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="content">
      <main class="section">
        <div class="card legal">
          <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
          <p class="legal-meta">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>

          <p>
            Welcome to ShowShowShow. These Terms of Service (“Terms”) are a legal agreement
            between you and ShowShowShow (“ShowShowShow,” “we,” “us,” or “our”) and govern your
            use of our website, app at <a href={appUrl}>{appUrl}</a>, and related services
            (together, the “Service”). By creating an account or using the Service, you agree to
            these Terms. If you do not agree, please don’t use the Service.
          </p>

          <h2>1. What ShowShowShow is</h2>
          <p>
            ShowShowShow is a personal tool for tracking, organizing, and scheduling the shows,
            movies, and anime you want to watch. We display title information (such as artwork,
            descriptions, and episode data) sourced from third-party providers. We do not host,
            stream, or distribute any films, series, or other video content, and we are not
            affiliated with any streaming service, studio, or content provider.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Your account</h2>
          <p>
            You need an account to use most features. Accounts are created and secured through our
            authentication provider. You’re responsible for the information you provide, for
            keeping your login credentials secure, and for activity that happens under your
            account. You must be at least 13 years old (or the minimum age of digital consent in
            your country, if higher) to use the Service.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Subscriptions, billing &amp; auto-renewal</h2>
          <p>
            The Service offers free features and optional paid subscription plans. The features and
            fees of each plan are described at the point of purchase. By starting a paid
            subscription, you authorize us and our payment processor to charge the applicable fees
            to your payment method.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Auto-renewal:</strong> Paid subscriptions automatically renew at the end of
              each billing period (for example, monthly or annually) at the then-current price,
              <strong>until you cancel</strong>. We’ll charge your payment method on each renewal
              unless you cancel before it occurs.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Payments:</strong> Payments are processed by our third-party payment
              processor, Stripe. We don’t store your full payment card details.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Price changes:</strong> We may change subscription prices. If we do, the new
              price applies to future billing periods, and we’ll give you reasonable notice where
              required by law.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Cancellation &amp; refunds</h2>
          <p>
            You can cancel a paid subscription at any time from your account settings. When you
            cancel, you’ll keep paid access until the end of your current billing period, and you
            won’t be charged again after that.
          </p>
          <p>
            Except where required by applicable law, payments are non-refundable and we do not
            provide refunds or credits for partial billing periods or unused time.
            {/* TODO(founder): set your refund stance here. The line above is a common
                "no partial refunds" default; soften it if you prefer (e.g., a 7-day
                money-back window). Some jurisdictions grant statutory cancellation rights
                that override this. */}
          </p>

          <h2>5. Acceptable use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>use the Service for any unlawful purpose or in violation of these Terms;</li>
            <li>attempt to disrupt, overload, or gain unauthorized access to the Service or its systems;</li>
            <li>scrape, copy, or harvest data from the Service except as expressly permitted;</li>
            <li>resell, sublicense, or commercially exploit the Service without our permission; or</li>
            <li>upload content that is illegal, infringing, or violates the rights of others.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>6. Your content</h2>
          <p>
            Content you create in the Service — such as your library, lists, lineups, schedules,
            notes, and reviews — remains yours. You grant us the limited license needed to store
            and display it back to you in order to operate the Service. You’re responsible for the
            content you create.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Intellectual property</h2>
          <p>
            The Service itself — including its software, design, branding, and original content —
            is owned by ShowShowShow and protected by intellectual-property laws. Title metadata
            and artwork are the property of their respective owners and providers. Names of shows,
            movies, networks, and streaming services are trademarks of their respective owners; our
            use of them is for identification only and does not imply affiliation or endorsement.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Third-party services and content</h2>
          <p>
            The Service relies on third-party providers (for example, for authentication, payments,
            analytics, hosting, and title metadata) and may link to or surface third-party content
            and websites. We are not responsible for third-party services or content, and your use
            of them may be governed by their own terms.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Disclaimers</h2>
          <p>
            The Service is provided “as is” and “as available,” without warranties of any kind,
            whether express or implied, to the fullest extent permitted by law. We don’t warrant
            that the Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or that title information will
            always be accurate or complete.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, ShowShowShow will not be liable for any
            indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or for any loss of
            data, arising out of or relating to your use of the Service. Our total liability for any
            claim relating to the Service will not exceed the greater of the amount you paid us in
            the twelve months before the claim or USD $50.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            You may stop using the Service and delete your account at any time. We may suspend or
            terminate your access if you violate these Terms or if necessary to protect the Service
            or other users. Sections that by their nature should survive termination (such as
            intellectual property, disclaimers, and limitation of liability) will survive.
          </p>

          <h2>12. Changes to these Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms from time to time. When we do, we’ll update the effective date
            above and, where appropriate, notify you. Your continued use of the Service after changes
            take effect means you accept the updated Terms.
          </p>

          <h2>13. Governing law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by the laws of [your jurisdiction — e.g., your state/country],
            without regard to its conflict-of-laws rules.
            {/* TODO(founder): fill in your governing-law jurisdiction (where you/your business
                are based). */}
          </p>

          <h2>14. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these Terms? Email us at
            <a href="mailto:hello@showshowshow.app">hello@showshowshow.app</a>.
          </p>

          <div class="legal-back">
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/">Back to home</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .legal {
      max-width: 820px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      text-align: left;
      line-height: 1.65;
    }
    .legal h1 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-family: Sora, sans-serif;
    }
    .legal h2 {
      margin: 28px 0 8px;
      font-family: Sora, sans-serif;
      font-size: 1.15rem;
    }
    .legal p,
    .legal li {
      color: var(--soft-ink);
    }
    .legal ul {
      padding-left: 20px;
    }
    .legal li {
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    .legal-meta {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      opacity: 0.8;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
    .legal-back {
      margin-top: 32px;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
